==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Redmouth
<hw>Red"mouth`</hw> <pr>(-mouth`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any one of several species of marine food fishes of the genus
<gen>Diabasis</gen>, or <gen>Haemulon</gen>, of the Southern United
States, having the inside of the mouth bright red. Called also
<altname>flannelmouth</altname>, and <altname>grunt</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Redness</ent>⟦br⟧
